doc.previous: At this time the Australian domestic airline travel sector was dominated by Australian National Airways ANA established in 1936 by a consortium of British financed Australian shipowners The Chifley Federal Government was determined to establish a state owned airline to operate all domestic and international services It was eventually thwarted in this aim by the High Court of Australia and so it established Trans Australia Airlines TAA to operate in competition with ANA 2
